translate ru strings:

    old "The trickle of guests continued."
    new "The trickle of guests continued."

    old "So many faces, so many names. Nodding. Smiling."
    new "So many faces, so many names. Nodding. Smiling."

    old "She had won her war. Subdued a rebellion."
    new "She had won her war. Subdued a rebellion."

    old "Now they called her Regent. Some fools whispered Queen."
    new "Now they called her Regent. Some fools whispered Queen."

    old "Now they called her Queen. A princess no more."
    new "Now they called her Queen. A princess no more."

    old "If she was so powerful, Sarah wondered why she often seemed to feel as if she lived at the mercy of her schedule."
    new "If she was so powerful, Sarah wondered why she often seemed to feel as if she lived at the mercy of her schedule."

    old "Events to be planned. Council meetings to attend."
    new "Events to be planned. Council meetings to attend."

    old "There never seemed to be enough time in the day."
    new "There never seemed to be enough time in the day."

    old "Still, Sarah could only play at being frustrated. In truth she loved performing the role."
    new "Still, Sarah could only play at being frustrated. In truth she loved performing the role."

    old "It made her proud to see the changes that came over the country by her hand. To see it flourish."
    new "It made her proud to see the changes that came over the country by her hand. To see it flourish."

    old "And a part of her also hoped that somewhere her father might look down on her works and be proud."
    new "And a part of her also hoped that somewhere her father might look down on her works and be proud."

    old "That reminded her. She had been so busy lately, she had let her prayers slip."
    new "That reminded her. She had been so busy lately, she had let her prayers slip."

    old "Sarah was not a zealot by any means, perhaps not even fully religious, but a part of her did always hesitate about rejecting it altogether."
    new "Sarah was not a zealot by any means, perhaps not even fully religious, but a part of her did always hesitate about rejecting it altogether."

    old "What was the harm in praying, after all. It would be, if anything, a brief moment of peace."
    new "What was the harm in praying, after all. It would be, if anything, a brief moment of peace."

    old "Then again, she had more than enough work to do as well."
    new "Then again, she had more than enough work to do as well."

    old "Go pray in the chapel later"
    new "Go pray in the chapel later"

    old "It was decided. A brief moment of respite, away from all the business of ruling. It would to her good."
    new "It was decided. A brief moment of respite, away from all the business of ruling. It would to her good."

    old "Get some more rest"
    new "Get some more rest"

    old "There was no time to pray. What little free time she had, she should use for herself. Get some extra sleep."
    new "There was no time to pray. What little free time she had, she should use for herself. Get some extra sleep."

    old "Sarah forced herself to smile as another couple approached her."
    new "Sarah forced herself to smile as another couple approached her."

    old "Newly rich from the trade in dyed wools."
    new "Newly rich from the trade in dyed wools."

    old "She could see a stunned awe in their faces as she remembered their names."
    new "She could see a stunned awe in their faces as she remembered their names."

    old "Sarah watched as they shuffled away."
    new "Sarah watched as they shuffled away."

    old "Even the smallest gesture could have an impact. It was why every detail mattered."
    new "Even the smallest gesture could have an impact. It was why every detail mattered."

    old "Sarah looked over at her husband."
    new "Sarah looked over at her husband."

    old "Varga stood tall. Proud. Strong."
    new "Varga stood tall. Proud. Strong."

    old "Her love for the man had never faded, only grown stronger."
    new "Her love for the man had never faded, only grown stronger."

    old "In all the world, she knew there was nobody who quite knew her as he did."
    new "In all the world, she knew there was nobody who quite knew her as he did."

    old "Dear, you're staring."
    new "Dear, you're staring."

    old "At my husband. Who can blame me for that?"
    new "At my husband. Who can blame me for that?"

    old "She saw his embarassed smile on his face. Even after all these years."
    new "She saw his embarassed smile on his face. Even after all these years."

    old "Still, we have guests to entertain."
    new "Still, we have guests to entertain."

    old "She saw him gesture towards a new couple that approached."
    new "She saw him gesture towards a new couple that approached."

    old "Nobles, those who had taken the right side during the revolution and now saw their stars rise."
    new "Nobles, those who had taken the right side during the revolution and now saw their stars rise."

    old "Sarah smiled and thanked them for their bravery, courage, loyalty. Was there any word of praise she spared them?"
    new "Sarah smiled and thanked them for their bravery, courage, loyalty. Was there any word of praise she spared them?"

    old "Their faces beamed."
    new "Their faces beamed."

    old "A new couple approached."
    new "A new couple approached."

    old "Sarah followed them as they thanked her and continued to walk."
    new "Sarah followed them as they thanked her and continued to walk."

    old "Even now, there was something about the peacefulness that unsettled her."
    new "Even now, there was something about the peacefulness that unsettled her."

    old "In her youth, her life had seemed perfect. The sudden death of her mother had shattered that child's idea of peace."
    new "In her youth, her life had seemed perfect. The sudden death of her mother had shattered that child's idea of peace."

    old "When she had imagined years later that peace had returned, the death of her father and everything that followed, upset it again."
    new "When she had imagined years later that peace had returned, the death of her father and everything that followed, upset it again."

    old "Now Sarah looked across the room and saw peace."
    new "Now Sarah looked across the room and saw peace."

    old "But she knew peace was often a prelude for conflict."
    new "But she knew peace was often a prelude for conflict."

    old "Or perhaps peace was a prelude for peace, and she tortured herself because she couldn't stand being content."
    new "Or perhaps peace was a prelude for peace, and she tortured herself because she couldn't stand being content."

    old "Sarah looked at Varga, suddenly snapped from her thoughts."
    new "Sarah looked at Varga, suddenly snapped from her thoughts."

    old "Ooh...yes. Was I acting strange?"
    new "Ooh...yes. Was I acting strange?"

    old "No stranger than usual."
    new "No stranger than usual."

    old "Sarah smiled back at him and turned back to her duties."
    new "Sarah smiled back at him and turned back to her duties."

    old "As time dragged on and the river of faces became and ocean, Sarah finally saw a chance to break away from the crowd."
    new "As time dragged on and the river of faces became and ocean, Sarah finally saw a chance to break away from the crowd."

    old "She left Varga by himself to deal with all the visitors."
    new "She left Varga by himself to deal with all the visitors."

    old "Sarah made a note to herself to apologize to him later."
    new "Sarah made a note to herself to apologize to him later."

    old "Walking through the crowd, Sarah looked about."
    new "Walking through the crowd, Sarah looked about."

    old "Everywhere, smiling faces greeted. Most raised a toast, and she casually nodded in thanks."
    new "Everywhere, smiling faces greeted. Most raised a toast, and she casually nodded in thanks."

    old "If she wanted peace, she'd have to break away from the crowd."
    new "If she wanted peace, she'd have to break away from the crowd."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah saw the face she hoped for."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah saw the face she hoped for."

    old "The years had weighed heavy on her brother, transforming him from the boy she knew to a young man."
    new "The years had weighed heavy on her brother, transforming him from the boy she knew to a young man."

    old "Young in age, but old in body. In spirit, he had always been near a hundred."
    new "Young in age, but old in body. In spirit, he had always been near a hundred."

    old "The trauma of his capture at the hands of Marion had forever broken something in him."
    new "The trauma of his capture at the hands of Marion had forever broken something in him."

    old "Though the pieces of Thomas were now back together, he was like a mirror shattered, impossible to be truly made whole again."
    new "Though the pieces of Thomas were now back together, he was like a mirror shattered, impossible to be truly made whole again."

    old "Still, he smiled, and she saw it was genuine. He was having a good day."
    new "Still, he smiled, and she saw it was genuine. He was having a good day."

    old "Sneaking away from your duties, are we?"
    new "Sneaking away from your duties, are we?"

    old "Sarah walked up to her brother."
    new "Sarah walked up to her brother."

    old "You're one to speak. Maybe I should remind them whose really king."
    new "You're one to speak. Maybe I should remind them whose really king."

    old "Please don't. I'm quite content here to be left alone."
    new "Please don't. I'm quite content here to be left alone."

    old "Ooh, am I intruding on your solitude?"
    new "Ooh, am I intruding on your solitude?"

    old "Thomas eyed her, his deep blue eyes that could never tell a proper lie."
    new "Thomas eyed her, his deep blue eyes that could never tell a proper lie."

    old "Never you, Sister. I can't stand most, and I can only endure a few. But you alone I actually enjoy."
    new "Never you, Sister. I can't stand most, and I can only endure a few. But you alone I actually enjoy."

    old "Thomas chuckled."
    new "Thomas chuckled."

    old "Well, you and the children, I suppose. They're alright too."
    new "Well, you and the children, I suppose. They're alright too."

    old "As a man, many of the features that plagued Thomas as a boy had only become more expressed in him."
    new "As a man, many of the features that plagued Thomas as a boy had only become more expressed in him."

    old "He liked books before, now he devoured them. He was quiet as a child, now he seemed most days turned entirely inward."
    new "He liked books before, now he devoured them. He was quiet as a child, now he seemed most days turned entirely inward."

    old "But one new feature of him was his love for his niece and nephew, Orwen and Miriam. Her children."
    new "But one new feature of him was his love for his niece and nephew, Orwen and Miriam. Her children."

    old "If they ever heard you speak ill of them, I don't think they'd ever recover. You really are their favorite person."
    new "If they ever heard you speak ill of them, I don't think they'd ever recover. You really are their favorite person."

    old "Please, they have a father too. And you for a mother. I suspect I hardly rank anywhere close."
    new "Please, they have a father too. And you for a mother. I suspect I hardly rank anywhere close."

    old "Yes, but when they are poorly behaved it's me or Varga who has to discipline them."
    new "Yes, but when they are poorly behaved it's me or Varga who has to discipline them."

    old "To them, you're just the fun uncle who can do no wrong and never punishes them."
    new "To them, you're just the fun uncle who can do no wrong and never punishes them."

    old "Thomas smiled as she spoke."
    new "Thomas smiled as she spoke."

    old "Yeah, I suppose that might be true. The truth is I'd let them get away with just about anything..."
    new "Yeah, I suppose that might be true. The truth is I'd let them get away with just about anything..."

    old "His voice wandered."
    new "His voice wandered."

    old "Don't tell them of course, before they run wild."
    new "Don't tell them of course, before they run wild."

    old "Spoil them, Thomas. It's what an uncle is for."
    new "Spoil them, Thomas. It's what an uncle is for."

    old "Sarah looked at Thomas, casually nursing his cup of wine. When he first returned, a gathering like this would have been too much for him."
    new "Sarah looked at Thomas, casually nursing his cup of wine. When he first returned, a gathering like this would have been too much for him."

    old "You're doing alright with all this?"
    new "You're doing alright with all this?"

    old "Thomas shrugged."
    new "Thomas shrugged."

    old "I manage. That counts as a good day for me."
    new "I manage. That counts as a good day for me."

    old "I'm happy to see you doing better. You know if you ever do feel up to it-"
    new "I'm happy to see you doing better. You know if you ever do feel up to it-"

    old "Sarah could not even finish her sentence before Thomas cut her off."
    new "Sarah could not even finish her sentence before Thomas cut her off."

    old "Please, Sarah. Don't even bring up the thought. This king business...I never had the stomach for it, not really."
    new "Please, Sarah. Don't even bring up the thought. This king business...I never had the stomach for it, not really."

    old "Everything is going well. You will continue as you are, and I will sign some paperwork once a week."
    new "Everything is going well. You will continue as you are, and I will sign some paperwork once a week."

    old "Sarah thought of raising an objection, but she could see her brother was determined. He really wanted no part in it."
    new "Sarah thought of raising an objection, but she could see her brother was determined. He really wanted no part in it."

    old "Alright Thomas, I understand. I won't bring it up again."
    new "Alright Thomas, I understand. I won't bring it up again."

    old "The two siblings stood in silence for a brief moment."
    new "The two siblings stood in silence for a brief moment."

    old "What I will bring up again though..."
    new "What I will bring up again though..."

    old "NO!"
    new "NO!"

    old "Thomas' voice shot up, catching the attention of some of the guests, before he quickly lowered his voice."
    new "Thomas' voice shot up, catching the attention of some of the guests, before he quickly lowered his voice."

    old "Please, Sarah, not again!"
    new "Please, Sarah, not again!"

    old "She suddenly pointed off in a direction."
    new "She suddenly pointed off in a direction."

    old "That's the daughter of Lady Morrel, Nancy Morrel. Doesn't she look cute?"
    new "That's the daughter of Lady Morrel, Nancy Morrel. Doesn't she look cute?"

    old "Sarah, please..."
    new "Sarah, please..."

    old "Thomas' voice turned into a whimper."
    new "Thomas' voice turned into a whimper."

    old "Sarah pointed out the next girl."
    new "Sarah pointed out the next girl."

    old "Or maybe you're more favorable to Tammy Rivers. Her family owns a large estate up from the capital, I heard it's beautiful."
    new "Or maybe you're more favorable to Tammy Rivers. Her family owns a large estate up from the capital, I heard it's beautiful."

    old "Why do you enjoy bullying me so?"
    new "Why do you enjoy bullying me so?"

    old "I'm not bullying, Thomas. You're a grown man. King to match. If you wanted to, you could have any one of them."
    new "I'm not bullying, Thomas. You're a grown man. King to match. If you wanted to, you could have any one of them."

    old "To do what with?"
    new "To do what with?"

    old "Sarah grinned playfully."
    new "Sarah grinned playfully."

    old "Well, I mean, that's between a man and his wife, none of my business."
    new "Well, I mean, that's between a man and his wife, none of my business."

    old "Thomas sighed."
    new "Thomas sighed."

    old "That's not what I meant!"
    new "That's not what I meant!"

    old "I mean, what is a girl like going to do with someone like me?"
    new "I mean, what is a girl like going to do with someone like me?"

    old "She's pretty, lively, happy."
    new "She's pretty, lively, happy."

    old "A girl like that needs someone who can make her happy. Not to be married off to a depressive like me."
    new "A girl like that needs someone who can make her happy. Not to be married off to a depressive like me."

    old "Sarah eyed her brother."
    new "Sarah eyed her brother."

    old "So you think she's pretty?"
    new "So you think she's pretty?"

    old "No, Sarah, no!"
    new "No, Sarah, no!"

    old "Before her brother could say much more, Sarah had snatched away Tammy Rivers from among her parents and dragged her towards Thomas."
    new "Before her brother could say much more, Sarah had snatched away Tammy Rivers from among her parents and dragged her towards Thomas."

    old "Sarah smiled as she saw the girl awkwardly introduce herself to Thomas, and Thomas more awkardly to her."
    new "Sarah smiled as she saw the girl awkwardly introduce herself to Thomas, and Thomas more awkardly to her."

    old "Enjoying the chaos she'd started, Sarah quickly escaped back into the crowd."
    new "Enjoying the chaos she'd started, Sarah quickly escaped back into the crowd."

    old "Sarah continued weaving her way through the busy crowd."
    new "Sarah continued weaving her way through the busy crowd."

    old "Slowly making her way towards one of the side doors, hoping for an escape."
    new "Slowly making her way towards one of the side doors, hoping for an escape."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah caught a familiar face from the corner of her eye."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah caught a familiar face from the corner of her eye."

    old "Sneaking out, are we?"
    new "Sneaking out, are we?"

    old "Wish that I were. Sadly my own guards appear too skilled to let me slip by."
    new "Wish that I were. Sadly my own guards appear too skilled to let me slip by."

    old "Lily smiled at the compliment."
    new "Lily smiled at the compliment."

    old "To be fair, you are easy to spot in a crowd."
    new "To be fair, you are easy to spot in a crowd."

    old "How have you been?"
    new "How have you been?"

    old "It had been a few weeks since she had last seen Lily."
    new "It had been a few weeks since she had last seen Lily."

    old "The girl had taken over as head of the Highfield family, ever since the rest of them had been cut down in the rebellion."
    new "The girl had taken over as head of the Highfield family, ever since the rest of them had been cut down in the rebellion."

    old "Though by Sarah's decree she was the head of it, the truth was that the family was a pit of vipers."
    new "Though by Sarah's decree she was the head of it, the truth was that the family was a pit of vipers."

    old "The Highfield family tree ran long and wide, and there seemed an endless number of branches, each of varying loyalty."
    new "The Highfield family tree ran long and wide, and there seemed an endless number of branches, each of varying loyalty."

    old "Poor Lily, never prepared for a life of such politics, had nearly drowned in the pit."
    new "Poor Lily, never prepared for a life of such politics, had nearly drowned in the pit."

    old "The solution had come when Spymaster Kravel had taken the poor girl under his wing, helping her navigate her new circumstances."
    new "The solution had come when Spymaster Kravel had taken the poor girl under his wing, helping her navigate her new circumstances."

    old "Now, Lily was still often plagued by busy work, but at least she could occasionally visit Sarah."
    new "Now, Lily was still often plagued by busy work, but at least she could occasionally visit Sarah."

    old "As well as could be expected."
    new "As well as could be expected."

    old "Had to listen to two families dispute a plot of land they supposedly both lived on forever."
    new "Had to listen to two families dispute a plot of land they supposedly both lived on forever."

    old "And?"
    new "And?"

    old "We sat around a map for nearly a week, drawing lines until finally we managed a divison both could live with."
    new "We sat around a map for nearly a week, drawing lines until finally we managed a divison both could live with."

    old "Land disputes, yes I'm well aware. Not the most exciting, but they do seem to cause the most drama."
    new "Land disputes, yes I'm well aware. Not the most exciting, but they do seem to cause the most drama."

    old "I get it. They need the farmland to live, and neither family was all that rich."
    new "I get it. They need the farmland to live, and neither family was all that rich."

    old "Still, it's days like that where I wish I was fighting in a war or something."
    new "Still, it's days like that where I wish I was fighting in a war or something."

    old "Sarah hushed her."
    new "Sarah hushed her."

    old "Don't say such things. You'll invite bad luck."
    new "Don't say such things. You'll invite bad luck."

    old "Lily chuckled."
    new "Lily chuckled."

    old "I forget you can be superstitious like that."
    new "I forget you can be superstitious like that."

    old "Sarah felt her face run red."
    new "Sarah felt her face run red."

    old "I'm not! I just...don't taunt the Fates is all I say."
    new "I'm not! I just...don't taunt the Fates is all I say."

    old "Lily grinned."
    new "Lily grinned."

    old "Sure, whatever you say, your Highness."
    new "Sure, whatever you say, your Highness."

    old "Sarah looked at the girl and remembered their brief encounter many years ago."
    new "Sarah looked at the girl and remembered their brief encounter many years ago."

    old "Did Lily remember the same?"
    new "Did Lily remember the same?"

    old "It seemed impossible that she couldn't, but perhaps for Lily such things were more common."
    new "It seemed impossible that she couldn't, but perhaps for Lily such things were more common."

    old "Was she being silly?"
    new "Was she being silly?"

    old "You're staring at me."
    new "You're staring at me."

    old "Ooh, I'm sorry I was just...my mind was wandering."
    new "Ooh, I'm sorry I was just...my mind was wandering."

    old "Perhaps we need an extra royal guard to keep track of your head?"
    new "Perhaps we need an extra royal guard to keep track of your head?"

    old "Sarah made a sour face."
    new "Sarah made a sour face."

    old "Very funny."
    new "Very funny."

    old "Ask her to sneak away with you"
    new "Ask her to sneak away with you"

    old "Lily..."
    new "Lily..."

    old "Would you want to get into some trouble?"
    new "Would you want to get into some trouble?"

    old "Lily frowned."
    new "Lily frowned."

    old "What are you suggesting?"
    new "What are you suggesting?"

    old "If I stay here much longer I might actually go insane. Meet me later in the gardens, near the northern ramparts."
    new "If I stay here much longer I might actually go insane. Meet me later in the gardens, near the northern ramparts."

    old "She saw Lily's hesitant face. Then she slowly nodded."
    new "She saw Lily's hesitant face. Then she slowly nodded."

    old "Sure. But if I actually end up in trouble..."
    new "Sure. But if I actually end up in trouble..."

    old "Well I'm in charge, so you might actually get in trouble of you don't show up."
    new "Well I'm in charge, so you might actually get in trouble of you don't show up."

    old "Sarah stuck out her tongue."
    new "Sarah stuck out her tongue."

    old "Lily rolled her eyes."
    new "Lily rolled her eyes."

    old "What would the people say if they knew they were ruled over by a brat?"
    new "What would the people say if they knew they were ruled over by a brat?"

    old "Let the matter rest"
    new "Let the matter rest"

    old "For a moment, Sarah thought about asking Lily to leave the party with her."
    new "For a moment, Sarah thought about asking Lily to leave the party with her."

    old "Then she thought better of it. She was letting her idleness get the better of her."
    new "Then she thought better of it. She was letting her idleness get the better of her."

    old "With the crowd in the room growing ever more, Sarah quickly waved goodbye to Lily."
    new "With the crowd in the room growing ever more, Sarah quickly waved goodbye to Lily."

    old "She wanted to get out, find a little space to breathe."
    new "She wanted to get out, find a little space to breathe."

    old "Smiling, waving, turning, spinning."
    new "Smiling, waving, turning, spinning."

    old "The whole thing was nearly like a dance, but ever so slowly, Sarah made her way towards one of the side doors to the Great Hall."
    new "The whole thing was nearly like a dance, but ever so slowly, Sarah made her way towards one of the side doors to the Great Hall."

    old "She quickly stepped through it."
    new "She quickly stepped through it."

    old "Instantly, all the noise and heat from the packed room was gone. It was even darker, out here without all those thousands of candles."
    new "Instantly, all the noise and heat from the packed room was gone. It was even darker, out here without all those thousands of candles."

    old "Sarah began to walk, taking in the peace."
    new "Sarah began to walk, taking in the peace."

    old "She had been in that room for so long, plagued by so much noise that the sudden silence felt like a blessing."
    new "She had been in that room for so long, plagued by so much noise that the sudden silence felt like a blessing."

    old "Sarah remembered her intention to go praying."
    new "Sarah remembered her intention to go praying."

    old "She began to walk down the empty hallway towards where the chapel was."
    new "She began to walk down the empty hallway towards where the chapel was."

    old "Sarah wanted some peace and decided to keep walking down the empty hallway."
    new "Sarah wanted some peace and decided to keep walking down the empty hallway."

    old "Suddenly, a sound from her left corner caught her attention."
    new "Suddenly, a sound from her left corner caught her attention."

    old "Sarah slightly jumped, startled by the noise."
    new "Sarah slightly jumped, startled by the noise."

    old "You never did do well with those crowds."
    new "You never did do well with those crowds."

    old "Sarah saw Lady Carolyn, her white teeth cutting through the dark, a meaningful smile."
    new "Sarah saw Lady Carolyn, her white teeth cutting through the dark, a meaningful smile."

    old "Why do you enjoy lurking in the shadows so much?"
    new "Why do you enjoy lurking in the shadows so much?"

    old "All the best things happen in the dark, don't you know?"
    new "All the best things happen in the dark, don't you know?"

    old "Sarah felt her face go red, the innuendo not lost on her."
    new "Sarah felt her face go red, the innuendo not lost on her."

    old "Flashes of memories run through her mind."
    new "Flashes of memories run through her mind."

    old "Those times when she had allowed Lady Carolyn to go too far with her."
    new "Those times when she had allowed Lady Carolyn to go too far with her."

    old "It had begun years ago...a moment of trust turned into something more."
    new "It had begun years ago...a moment of trust turned into something more."

    old "Ever since, though ruling kept her occupied, there would be moments where she would find herself drawn to Lady Carolyn's room."
    new "Ever since, though ruling kept her occupied, there would be moments where she would find herself drawn to Lady Carolyn's room."

    old "A meeting between the two, running late."
    new "A meeting between the two, running late."

    old "When they had crossed lines no women should cross..."
    new "When they had crossed lines no women should cross..."

    old "Sarah knew it was wrong, or at least, she knew it only because she had been told as much all her life."
    new "Sarah knew it was wrong, or at least, she knew it only because she had been told as much all her life."

    old "Whenever she found herself back in Lady Carolyn's room, the ideas of right and wrong felt so hollow. Meaningless."
    new "Whenever she found herself back in Lady Carolyn's room, the ideas of right and wrong felt so hollow. Meaningless."

    old "Instead, she found herself hopelessly lost to her."
    new "Instead, she found herself hopelessly lost to her."

    old "Everyone treated her as a ruler. Someone of importance."
    new "Everyone treated her as a ruler. Someone of importance."

    old "Lady Carolyn was the only one who seemed able to look through the illusion and see who she really was. Who didn't treat her as if she was more than human."
    new "Lady Carolyn was the only one who seemed able to look through the illusion and see who she really was. Who didn't treat her as if she was more than human."

    old "Perhaps it was because she had seen her grow up around the castle and knew that so much of what Sarah pretended to be was just that, pretend."
    new "Perhaps it was because she had seen her grow up around the castle and knew that so much of what Sarah pretended to be was just that, pretend."

    old "Regardless, their sessions, though sparing, had continued across the years."
    new "Regardless, their sessions, though sparing, had continued across the years."

    old "Well, shouldn't you be inside? Entertaining our guests?"
    new "Well, shouldn't you be inside? Entertaining our guests?"

    old "I should be inside. You should be inside."
    new "I should be inside. You should be inside."

    old "Yet here we are, both poorly doing our jobs."
    new "Yet here we are, both poorly doing our jobs."

    old "Yes, I suppose you're right that I don't have much of a leg to stand on."
    new "Yes, I suppose you're right that I don't have much of a leg to stand on."

    old "Well, you are the ruler of our fair nation. The truth is you don't really owe an explanation to anyone."
